package.json
> this is entry point to the app
> meta data (like version, description)
> scripts (start, test,build)
> packages

//steps to generate package.json
> Go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> type npm init
> Answer all questions
> type yes

//steps to install packages
> Go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm install packagename


local dependency
> only related to the folder
> can only be used in same folder
> added in package.json
> open cmd and go inside the folder where you want to install
> npm i package

dev dependency
> all thing same like local dependency
> only need at the time of development
> open cmd and go inside the folder where you want to install
> npm i packagename --save-dev

global dependency
> install in laptop drive instend of application folder
> independent of application 
> only used generating , run app
> we need admin permission to install
> only accesible befor app start

# window
> open cmd as admin
> npm i -g packagename

# mac/linux
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g packagename

# nodemon
* Only one time in laptop
> open cmd as admin
> npm i -g nodemon

# Setup mongodb



Params
> What we pass after /
> We need to declare in route
> if declare then complusory to pass

QueryParams
> What we pass after ?
> No need to declare
> No need to pass
